<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2621"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2621-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2621">Truth is the only real 'Open'&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">sbishop</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Apparently lying to Congress is a crime, but how many folks have served time for this crime.  I would propose an active government department, with the help of all the NGOs out there, to prosecute anyone lying in Congress.  I think if a person knowingly lies they should go to jail and if they are a member of Congress they should lose their seat.  If they unknowingly lie they should be forced to apologize and state the truth to the open session of Congress.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2621" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2621', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=2621')">Comments (4)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2621"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=truth congress">truth congress</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2621"></div>
