<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2620"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2620-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2620">On/off-the-record rule&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3957-4049">lbaskett</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">We propose a new guideline regarding whether a government official should talk to the press on- or off-the-record:<br/><br/>Any government official who gives a reporter information that supports the government's position should be considered "on-the-record," i.e. the reporter should be able to source the information to the official.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2620" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2620', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2237&topicID=2620')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2620"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=press">press</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=media">media</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=off-the-record">off-the-record</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=attribution">attribution</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2620"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
